^b@2^*bdjneill:^*n  Welcome all to Standard Modern Precision

As I mentioned in the textbook ^*h http://www.bridgewithdan.com/systems/index.html ^*nclick here^*x, it's fun, effective, legal, and really going to be the standard for the future as far as precision in the States.  Most of the top pros have at least one partnership in which they play this system.   So it's nice to be able to learn a little about it.       You may even use it.

For today, North is the dealer
The two main areas I will go over today are:

1) Overview of the openings

2) 1@C - 1@D continuations

In the future weeks we will look at all other parts of the system.   To start, let's look at North (opener) hands

In precision we open ALL eleven's and many 10's.   What this does is it allows us to open more frequently than most, and put pressure on the opponents.

