realrowdy:  It seems to free up your bidding.
wyoming33: What if you have 5M and 5m do you then open the major? And why not the major when you had 5/6?
djneill:  Yes if you have 5M-5m you open the major (if 11-15 HCP)
Well, in precision, you take a gamble with 6-5's to always open the 6, and then catch up later in the 5

Somebody asked: - Is it HCP or distributional points?
The 11-15 is a guideline. Feel free to use your judgement with distribution, but we open ALL 11's
There is no 11 we do not open.

