Redbird44:  Do you count quacks when opening light?
djneill:  Yes you count every HCP, even the quacks
Feel free to use judgement if your hand looks stinky, it probably is not worth opening.

But personally, I've opened all 11's and will continue
lots of 10's, some 9's!
Once even a 6 HCP hand but that was questionable :-)
wyoming33: We know you are aggressive Dan :)

djneill:  Well, 6-6 shape 6 HCP, I figure 6-6-6 is a special number
I would never open a 6 HCP hand unless I felt it was a freak of freaks

Precision lowers the bar though, enough to open light more often than in 2/1 or SAYC
And since the maximum is 15, partner will never take you for a monster,
so you can get away with a lot.
